                        <!--
                            2026-05-05 (iter 193): per-unit Combat Lua native UX.
                            Surfaces iter-154 LIVE wires that have been queued
                            since they shipped: Heal (no-arg), TakeDamage (float-arg),
                            SetDamageModifier (float-arg), SetRateOfFireModifier (float-arg).
                            All take a unit Lua expression + (for 3 of 4) a single
                            float arg. Distinct from the per-slot scalars above —
                            these target a SPECIFIC unit by Lua expression instead
                            of operating on every unit owned by a slot.
                        -->
                        <!-- 2026-05-07 (iter 378): UX polish — header was stale at "(iter 193 — iter 154 LIVE wires)"
                             which implies all wires from iter-154; section actually mixes iter-154 (4 wires:
                             Heal/Take_Damage/Set_Damage_Modifier/Set_Rate_Of_Fire_Modifier) + iter-162 (Suspend_AI).
                             iter-193 was the surfacing-iter codename — internal noise to operators. -->
                        <GroupBox Header="Per-unit combat actions (5 LIVE wires)">
